text:
I also noticed that the NativeTextHandler always writes the graphics current AffineTransform (which often is the identity matrix).

It would be nice if the NativeTextHandler checks if it really has to write the graphics current AffineTransform (as in the different draw method of PSGraphics):
boolean newTransform = gen.getCurrentState().checkTransform(trans)
        && !trans.isIdentity();
if (newTransform) {
    gen.concatMatrix(trans);
}
